title: warthog
body:
A type of wild [[boar]] that lives in open and semi-open habitats, even in quite arid regions, in sub-Saharan [[Africa]]. The two species of warthogs were formerly considered conspecific under the scientific name [i]Phacochoerus aethiopicus[/i], but today this is limited to the [[desert]] warthog.

* [b]Common warthog[/b] ([i]Phacochoerus africanus[/i]). The best-known, most widespread species. Widespread in the [[savannah]] of Sub-Saharan Africa from Senegal to Ethiopia down to South Africa, absent from heavily forested or desert areas.
* [b]Desert warthog[/b] ([i]Phacochoerus aethiopicus[/i]). Its distribution ranges from Northern Kenya and Somalia, and possibly Djibouti, Eritrea, and Ethiopia.

Warthogs are seen covered in earthy brown bristly hairs, their bodies and heads appear largely naked from a distance, with only the crest along the back, and the tufts on their cheeks and tails being obviously haired. The term [i]warthog[/i] refers to their facial wattles, which are particularly distinct in males. They also have very distinct [[tusks]], which reach a length of 25 to 64 centimetres in the males, but are always smaller in the females. Warthogs are omnivorous, with most of their diet consist of plant materials and occasionally eat small [[animal]]s.

* [[Pumbaa]], the main character of [[The Lion King]] is a warthog.
* [b]Hoglin[/b], a large hostile mob in [[Minecraft]] that spawns in the Nether dimension strongly resembles the warthog.

title: deadmau5
body:
Joel Thomas Zimmerman (born January 5, 1981),[2] known professionally as Deadmau5 (stylized as deadmau5; pronounced "dead-mouse"), is a Canadian electronic music producer and DJ. He mainly produces progressive house music, though he also produces and DJs other genres of electronic music, including techno under the alias Testpilot. Zimmerman has received six Grammy Award nominations for his work.

He has worked with other DJs and producers, such as Kaskade, Wolfgang Gartner, Rob Swire, and Chris Lake. He has also collaborated with Steve Duda under the group name BSOD (Better Sounding On Drugs), and was part of the group named WTF? with Duda, Tommy Lee and DJ Aero. In 2007, he founded his own record label, Mau5trap. Deadmau5 is currently one of the highest paid electronic music producers in the world,[3] and is a masked music artist similar to Marshmello and Daft Punk.[4] His works have been included in compilation albums such as Tiësto's In Search of Sunrise 6: Ibiza, and presented on Armin van Buuren's A State of Trance radio show.

title: help:saved_searches
body:
Saved searches allow you to save frequently used tag searches. They also provide a convenient way to check for new posts under a given search. Using saved searches, you can find updates by your favorite artists, characters, pools, or [[help:cheatsheet|anything else you can search for]].

h4. Adding a search

* Perform a search from the "posts":/posts page.
* Click the "Save search" button under the Options header in the menu to the left of the search results.
* Optionally name your search in the Labels section of the dialogue box that appears.
* Click "Submit".

h4. Viewing searches

To check for new posts among your saved searches, visit your user profile by following the My Account link in the navbar.

h4. Editing searches

To manage your existing saved searches, visit your "saved searches":/saved_searches page.

h4. Features

The following represents the current functionality of saved searches:

* Each saved search will return the most recent 1,000 posts matching that tag query.
* A saved search can have several labels. Labels allow you to organize your saved searches into different groups.
* If you have a gold account, you can view all posts for a single category, or across all saved searches.
* Saved searches are updated once an hour.
* Platinum users can have at most 1,000 saved searches, Builder users can have unlimited saved searches, and everyone else can have at most 250 saved searches.

h4. See also

* [[help:tag subscriptions]] - tag subscriptions have been replaced by saved searches.

title: mirai_shounen_conan
body:
[i][b]Future Boy Conan[/b][/i] (未来少年コナン [i]Mirai Shōnen Konan[/i]) is a 70s post-apocalyptic [[science fiction]] anime series which premiered across Japan on the NHK network between April 4 and October 31, 1978 on the Tuesday 19:30-20:00 timeslot. The official English title used by Nippon Animation is [i][b]Conan, The Boy in Future[/b][/i].

The anime is set in a post-apocalyptic Earth covered almost entirely by water, a result of the terrible and advanced electromagnetic weaponry used during World War III. 

Spanning a total of 26 episodes, the series was produced by Nippon Animation and featured [[miyazaki_hayao_(person)|Miyazaki Hayao]] (director, character designs, storyboards), Takahata Isao (storyboards) and [[Tomino Yoshiyuki]] (storyboards). It is an adaptation of "Alexander Key":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Key 's 1970 Sci-Fi novel [i]"The Incredible Tide":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Incredible_Tide [/i].

A [[video game]] version of the series by Telenet Japan was released in 1992 on NEC's [[PC Engine]] console. The game was released on the Super CD-Rom format and was only available in Japan. A [[PlayStation 2]] action and adventure game adaptation was also released in 2005 only in Japan.

title: eye_chart
body:
An eye chart is a standardized test used to measure a person's visual acuity. Consists of a table of characters of decreasing size, usually from the top down. The test taker then identifies the characters until they become too small for them to do so.

Common in Japan is the [[Landolt C]] test, where the chart contains circles with small gaps and the subject has to determine on which side the gap lies. Eye charts that use Latin letters, such as the "Snellen chart":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snellen_chart or "LogMAR chart":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LogMAR_chart", are common in countries that use the Latin alphabet.

Visual acuity is measured by two numbers, where the first number is the distance the subject needs to read something and the second number is the distance a normal person needs. In America, it is standard for the first number to be 20 (feet), with 20/20 being normal vision. In Japan and countries that use the metric system, the standard is 6 (meters), with normal vision being 6/6.

title: granzon
body:
The Granzon is one of the first machines developed by the Divine Crusaders. The design is planned out by [[Shu Shirakawa]], a member of the faction and a good friend of their leader, [[Bian Zoldark]]. The Granzon is so costly to develop and construct that it consumed two-thirds of the Divine Crusader's budget. It's also known that Shu used alchemy from La Gias to enhance the power of the Granzon.

The Granzon uses an antimatter annihilation engine, a perfectly efficient energy source. The annihilation engine is able to meet the immense energy requirements of the Granzon's weapon systems, which all involve gravity and time-space manipulation. An advanced artificial intelligence program also allows the Granzon to engage up to 65,536 enemies at once. So far, the only units said to be able to hold the Granzon one-on-one are the [[Astranagant]], Dis Astranagant, [[Shurouga]], [[Cybuster]] (in its full possession mode), and Zelvoid (in its full possession mode). 

Using the Kabbalah System Shu can turn the Granzon into the [[Neo Granzon]], one of the strongest mechs in the [[Super Robot Wars]] multiverse.

Before Seikima-II Demon Kogure had graduated with honors from Wasada University with honors.

title: english_electric_lightning
body:
The [b]English Electric Lightning[/b] is a [[jet]] fighter/interceptor aircraft developed by English Electric (later British Aerospace) for the Royal Air Force (RAF). It is visually distinctive for having its two jet engines stacked one on top of the other in the fuselage, rather than side-by-side as is seen in virtually every other twin-powered aircraft with internal engines. It is also notable for having both overwing and underwing hardpoints in its wings. 

h5. Background information
First flying in 1954, the Lightning was one of the earliest military aircraft to achieve speeds of Mach 2, and the first jet ever to achieve "supercruise" (supersonic flight without the use of afterburners). 

Though lightly armed with only two very short-range missiles and two cannons, the Lightning's high speed, even higher acceleration, fast climbing and agility made it very popular with pilots even long after it became obsolete, and assignments to Lightning squadrons were highly prized in the RAF. In 1988 the last Lightnings were finally retired and replaced by the [[Panavia tornado (aircraft)|Panavia Tornado ADV]].

body: A weapon designed to kill large animals, such as domestic cattle and horses, as quickly and (hopefully) painlessly as possible, by inflicting a concussion that instantly renders the animal unconscious. The most common type is the [i]captive bolt pistol[/i], which, as its name suggests, is a handgun-like device that forcibly projects a heavy bolt, which remains attached to the weapon. body:
Character from [[Granblue Fantasy]] who originated in [[Shingeki no Bahamut]] as the [i]Witchcrafter[/i]. She also appears in [[Shadowverse]], where her art from Shingeki no Bahamut is reused.

Age: Unknown
Height: 170 cm
Element: Fire, Earth (Christmas), Dark (Summer)
CV: [[Oohara Sayaka]] (JP, all appearances); unknown (EN)

Appearance-wise, Magisa has a [[curvy]] physique with a [[large breasts|voluptuous]] [[huge breasts|bosom]], [[thick thighs|shapely]] [[thighs]] and [[wide hips]]. She has [[very long hair|very long]] [[grey hair]], [[purple eyes]] and full [[lips]].

Magisa has two attires, both of which are [[backless outfit|backless]] and feature [[thighhighs]] with [[garter straps]]. In both attires, her signature [[witch hat]] stands out.
* The first is [[red dress|red]], and has her breasts covered in sheer fabric. She also wears wrist warmers around her wrists. Her hat is also red.
* The second is [[black dress|black]] and features a vertical-stripe pattern while revealing both [[cleavage]] and [[sideboob]], and a pair of [[elbow gloves]] now adorn her arms. She wears a few [[belt|belts]] around her waist for show, and a large [[black cape|black]] [[cape]] flows from her shoulders. Her iconic hat has turned black and features an elaborate motif on the inside of its brim.

Magisa is a sultry sorceress who one day receives a vision of Estalucia, the Island of the Astrals, where the [[Gran (Granblue Fantasy)|protag]][[Djeeta (Granblue Fantasy)|onist]] and their crew are headed. In her vision, Magisa saw [[Lyria (Granblue Fantasy)|Lyria]], and intended to claim the Girl in Blue to reach the Island of the Astrals. However, the captain convinces Magisa to join their crew, knowing their interests align.

Aside from her clairvoyance, Magisa relies on both her immense magical power and the aid of her demon familiar, [[Morax (Granblue Fantasy)|Morax]], a huge bovine creature of flame, on the field of battle. In gameplay, she can only summon Morax from Lv90 onward, requiring her to be 5* uncapped.

title: makishima_shougo
body: [b]Makishima Shougo (槙島 聖護)[/b] is a character from [[Psycho-Pass]]. The antagonist of the series, he is an enigmatic man who frequently quotes books. He is implicated in a number of otherwise unrelated murders (including the murder of Enforcer Sasayama), where he helped the perpetrators to get the resources needed to enact their crimes. Makishima is always judging people, and those who associate with him and fail to meet his expectations end up badly. The only people he seems to be on equal terms with are Choe Gu-Sung and Kouzaburou Touma, and he holds a particular curiosity for [[Kougami Shin'ya]]. Makishima's real intention is to destroy the Sibyl system and create what he believes will be a better world. His crime coefficient is at a steady low level even when killing, and he is an extremely competent martial artist. In episode 16 [spoiler]he was captured by Tsunemori Akane and taken into custody, but he manages to escape, armed with the knowledge of the true nature of Sibyl.[/spoiler]

title: squats_(warhammer_40k)
body:
The Squats were a race of Abhumans from [[Warhammer 40K]] based on the Dwarfs of Warhammer fantasy. Due to Games Workshop disliking how they were created, the Squats were made extinct in the 40k lore due to the [[Tyranid]]s invading the Squats homeworld. Despite this, many fans still love the Squats and wish to see them again in the current Warhammer 40k universe.

In 2022, the Squats were officially brought back to Warhammer 40k under the name,  [b]Leagues of Votann[/b]. Furthermore, it was explained in the new lore they were never extinct as the world that was invaded by the Tyranids was in fact one of the many worlds owned by the Leagues of Votann and miscommunication by the Imperium of Man led the latter to believe the Squats were killed off by the Tyranids.

title: treasure_(developer)
body:
[b]Treasure Co., Ltd.[/b] is a Japanese [[video game]] developer based in Tokyo known for its action, platform, and shoot 'em up games. 

The company was founded in 1992 by [[Konami]] employees seeking to explore original game concepts and free themselves from Konami's reliance on sequels. 

Their first game, [[Gunstar Heroes]] (1993) on the [[Sega Mega Drive]], was a critical success and established a creative and action-oriented design style that would continue to characterize their output. 

Treasure's philosophy in game development has always been to make games they enjoy, not necessarily those that have the greatest commercial viability.

Treasure grew a cult following for their action games developed during the 90s, and though initially exclusive to [[SEGA]] platforms, they expanded to other platforms in 1997. 

The company earned recognition from critics, being called one of the best Japanese indie studios and 2D game developers. The company's output decreased in the 2010s, with their most recent release being [[Gaist Crusher God]] in 2014.

title: yuri_eberwein
body:
Yuri in [[Mahou Shoujo Lyrical Nanoha A's Portable: The Gears of Destiny|The Gears of Destiny]], although Unbreakable Dark has been mentioned by the Materials in [[Mahou Shoujo Lyrical Nanoha A's Portable: The Battle of Aces|The Battle of Aces]].

Born in the Ancient Belkan ages, Yuri was originally a single entity. However, due to a program written with the aim of overwriting the Book of the Night Sky, Yuri was turned into Unbreakable Dark (砕け得ぬ闇 Kudake'enu Yami), aka System "Unbreakable Dark" (アンブレイカブル・ダーク Anbureikaburu Dāku) or U-D (Ｕ－Ｄ Yū Dī) and divided into multiple entities.

She is according to herself and the Materials: The True Darkness of the Book of Darkness and her Examia energies are responsible for the rampages of the Book of Darkness's Defense Program (the Materials themselves) that destroy worlds.

So uncontrollable are her powers that she and her Book of the Purple Sky were transferred into the Book of the Night Sky(which at the time was a Storage Device) causing parts of her program to segment into the Materials with Material-D which serves as the core of both the Defense Program and the Book of Darkness itself(outranking the Book's Master Control Program) segmenting further to create the Wolkenritter.

When battling Vivio Takamachi as U-D in 0066, she mistakes Vivio as the Heiliger Kaiser of the Cradle. From their conversation, it is also revealed that she knows Olivie Sägebrecht.

By the end of the Unbreakable Dark Incident, Yuri eventually has her Examia overwritten by Dearche(similar to how Hayate overwrote the Book of Darkness returning it to becoming the Book of the Night Sky) and is given back the name she had before splitting into U-D and the Materials.

Yuri in the movie continuity.

Near the end of Reflection, it is revealed by Iris (who calls Yuri a Demon) that she died during a disaster caused by Yuri decades ago, and now she is going to take revenge. When Yuri is unsealed/wakened from the Examia crystal, she is quickly mind-controlled by Iris with the virus codes before their conversion is finished, causing her to attack the Administrative Bureau mages including Fate T. Harlaown and Signum with Crystal Tree.

In Detonation, after Nanoha Takamachi comes to save the Administrative Bureau mages using Formula Cannon, Iris order Yuri to attack Nanoha. As Nanoha had activated System Alter, she is able to dodge Yuri's attack. The fight goes on until Nanoha's body gets injured due to the negative effect of System Alter which allows Yuri to land a finishing blow. Nanoha is then saved by Vita, Signum and Hayate. Soon, Iris order Yuri to leave the area.

Later, after Levi recovers one of Tome of the Night Sky's pages that Yuri wanted the others to have, a shared past from Yuri and Iris is shown. It is revealed that Iris first met Yuri in a small cave on Eltria 40 years ago. Yuri tries to speak with Iris while using Belka language but due to Iris not being able to understand, Yuri enables the Book of Darkness to activate the translation system so she can speak the same language as Iris. Yuri introduces herself as a guardian of the Book of Darkness; her duty is to watch over the tome to prevent NachtWal from going berserk and from killing its master. After their conversation, Yuri reveals an ability which leads the laboratory members to believe she is the key to revive Eltria, so they ask her to stay with them and Iris. The flashback is suddenly skipped to a scene in which Yuri seemingly killed Phil Maxwell and Iris. Yuri states they will meet again in the future. The Book of Darkness disappears alongside Yuri to another planet. It is also explained that the reason why Yuri didn't show up to stop NachtWal during the Book of Darkness incident was because the page that contained Yuri's guardian system got lost in the sea and transformed into a crystal after NachtWal was destroyed in space.

Soon, Iris orders Yuri to attack Tokyo along with the Iris Units. The three materials come to fight against Yuri. During the fight, the trio slowly regain their memories and remember that they were once cats who lived with Yuri and Iris. After the three materials take down Yuri, she breaks free from Iris' control. Suddenly, an android shows up and attacks the materials, severely injuring them. It's revealed that the android is Phil, the laboratory chief that was supposed killed by Yuri 40 years ago. Phil takes Yuri and flies toward the Tokyo Station. After receiving the mana energy from Stern and Levi, Dearche in Trinity Blood Form faces Yuri to save her from Phil's control. For a finishing move, Dearche begins to charge Excalibur Trinity. Yuri tells her to stop or she will transform back to her original cat form, but Dearche doesn't listen stating they wouldn't regret giving back all the love Yuri gave them back then. After successfuly casting the spell and transforming back to cat form, Yuri finally breaks free from Phil's control and embraces Dearche.

Near the end of Detonation, Yuri and the three materials go to Eltria along with the Florian sisters. While living together with the Florian family, Yuri and the others succesfully revive Eltria.

Yuri in [[Mahou Shoujo Lyrical Nanoha INNOCENT]].

Yuri Eberwein is an international student studying abroad in Uminari City.

title: shiritori
body:
A Japanese word game in which players take turns saying words whose first kana is same as the last kana of the previous player's word. For instance, someone might start with [i]ringo[/i] (りんご) and the next person might follow with [i]gomasuri[/i] (ごますり). A player who repeats a word is out. As there are no words that start with [i]n[/i] (ん), a player who uses a word ending in it, such as [i]mikan[/i] (みかん) is out.

h4. Strategies

h6. Letter frequency
A major shiritori strategy is to use words that end in a letter that appears much more frequently at the end of words than at the beginning. This makes it harder for the opponent to come up with words and easier for you.  By repeatedly using such a letter, the hope is that your opponent will run out of words.

In Japanese, popular letters to use with this strategy include [i]ru[/i] (る), [i]nu[/i] (ぬ), [i]pu[/i] (ぷ), and a few others. They are referred to as the "ru attack" (る攻め), "nu attack" (ぬ攻め), and so on. 
To take [i]pu[/i] as an example, [1] says there are about 700 Japanese words ending with [i]pu[/i] but only 160 starting with [i]pu[/i].

In English, [i]y[/i] works well with this strategy. [1]

h6. Countering
If your opponent is attacking you with a particular letter, then you can attempt to counter them using a word that both begins and ends with that letter. [2]

h6. Examples

* [i]ru[/i] attack
** [i][[Puchimasu!]][/i] season 2, episode 40   [Noted by user Elle Lowel at post #3030911, comment #1795085]

* [i]pu[/i] attack
** pool #13493, which is based on words [[Kanzaki Ranko]] used in [i][[Idolmaster Cinderella Girls]][/i] episode 8 (starts at 15m15s, video "here":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1ir3VUqWkmI]).

h4. Links

[1] "English shiritori analysis":[http://www.procrasist.com/entry/english-siritori]

[2] "A surefire way to win Shiritori":[https://matome.naver.jp/odai/2142409661773204801]

* "Blog post":[http://kudaranaihanashi.blog.shinobi.jp/%E5%A5%A5%E6%B7%B1%E3%81%8D%E6%97%A5%E6%9C%AC%E8%AA%9E/%E7%A7%98%E5%A5%A5%E7%BE%A9%E3%80%80-%E3%81%97%E3%82%8A%E3%81%A8%E3%82%8A%E5%BF%85%E5%8B%9D%E6%B3%95-] talking about Shiritori strategies, including [i]nu[/i], [i]ru[/i], and [i]pu[/i] attacks.

title: raven_cronwell
body:
[[Elsword]] character, his full name is Raven Cronwell. A warrior who fought to defend the Velder Kingdom but was horribly betrayed. A Nasod offered to help him in his quest for vengeance, and he agreed to have a prototype Nasod claw in place of his left arm. However, he met [[elsword (character)|Elsword]] and the others, and Raven now seeks to redeem himself. His seiyuu is [[Miyano Mamoru]].

title: elsword_(character)
body:
Eponymous hero of [[Elsword]], and younger brother of [[elesis (elsword)|Elesis]]. A hot-blooded knight who seeks to protect his kingdom while looking for his missing sister.

He is mentioned in Grand Chase as [[Elesis Sieghart]]'s brother. As a result, he is presumably called Elsword Sieghart, but [b]he is not the same character[/b] as this Elsword. His seiyuu is [[Suzumura Ken'ichi]].

title: rena_erindel
body:
[i][[Elsword]][/i] character, her full name is Rena Erindel. An elf who exists due to the power of El, but this energy is dwindling. If it fades completely, so will she, so she is on a quest to protect the El and her friends.

She is known for her large chest size, often bouncing during some of her stances. She's generally the big sister of the group, mediating [[Aisha Landar|Aisha]] and [[Elsword (character)|Elsword]]'s spats. Her seiyuu is [[Horie Yui]].

title: whiskey
body:
A distilled alcoholic spirit. Whiskey (also spelled "whisky" in much of the English-speaking world outside the United States) is made from fermented grain mash in a process that starts out similarly to the brewing of [[beer]], but it is then distilled and aged in a wooden cask, making the final product very different from beer. It is stored in glass bottles and is served in small glasses in small amounts due to its high alcoholic content. Popular types include bourbon, Scotch, and [[Jack Daniel's]] Tennessee whiskey.

title: spoken_sound_effect
body:
A [[sound effects|sound effect]] or onomatopoeia not normally spoken aloud that occurs inside a [[speech bubble]].

This is often used to draw the viewer's attention towards the sound made by an object or action, with the tail end of the speech bubble pointing towards the source of the sound. This has an effect as though the object is speaking - interrupting conversation or silence in a room.
